    },
    {
      "text": "Rip-Tide Racer is a 2000 video game developed and published by Cryo Interactive for the Game Boy Color. Players race futuristic hoverbikes named waterpods across eight courses. Upon release, the game received negative reviews, with most critics finding the game was difficult to control, and competing racers were too slow to be challenging.",
